## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the **React/Vite** pattern from the official Vercel documentation:

```javascript
import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';

export default function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      {/* App content */}
      <Analytics />
    </div>
  );
}
```

This pattern is correctly applied in two places:
1. In the Admin view (for admin page analytics)
2. In the main App view (for all other pages)

## Next Steps for Deployment

To enable Web Analytics on Vercel:

1. **Enable in Vercel Dashboard**:
   - Go to your project settings on Vercel
   - Navigate to the Analytics section
   - Click "Enable" to activate Web Analytics

2. **Deploy**:
   - Run `vercel deploy` or push to your connected Git repository
   - Vercel will automatically inject the analytics routes at `/_vercel/insights/*`

3. **Verify**:
   - After deployment, visit your site
   - Open browser DevTools → Network tab
   - Look for requests to `/_vercel/insights/view`
   - Check the Vercel dashboard for analytics data

## Notes

- No code changes were necessary as Analytics was already properly configured
